org.ndnx.ndn.impl.encoding
Interface XMLDecoder

All Known Implementing Classes:
BinaryXMLDecoder, GenericXMLDecoder, TextXMLDecoder
public interface XMLDecoder

Each XMLCodec consists effectively of an encoder/decoder pair. The decoder implements this interface, the encoder must implement XMLEncoder. These do the work of encoding or decoding content. The ndnb binary encoding supports only a number of simple types, all codecs are limited to these same types for simplicity.

pushXMLDictionary

void pushXMLDictionary(XMLDictionary dictionary)
Some codecs use a dictionary to make encoding and decoding more efficient. Those codecs typically load their default dictionary automatically. This call allows a user to manipulate the dictionary stack, adding their own dictionaries to the set used to decode.

Parameters:
dictionary - a dictionary to add to the set used for decoding

popXMLDictionary

XMLDictionary popXMLDictionary()
Some codecs use a dictionary to make encoding and decoding more efficient. Those codecs typically load their default dictionary automatically. This call allows a user to manipulate the dictionary stack, removing the most recently added dictionary from the set used to decode.

Returns:
returns the removed dictionary
